1, Check every function or class when you finish. The quality of a code is more important than the speed. 
   Keep in mind: the early mistake will always be expanded.
2, A good document and comments will never waste your time. 
3, If you use a function frequently, find a time to summary it into a library. It always turns to be a great gift for the later jobs and newer.
4, You will always forget the usage of a function or a class, so make a document for the frequent functions or classes, then you can move your attention on the design and algorithm.
5, A clear structure is more important than a good looking. Just like find your wife, pay more attention on her thought, not looking. 
6, Never give up and worry about learning. A siutable tools will improve your skill, and make the work easier.
